  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    AGR: Value Network View&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Value Network is inspired from Verna Alleeâ€™s Value Networks [Allee 2002]. It focuses on the Deliverable Flows that&#xD;
    occur between the Roles of a Collaboration. Such a view is shown in Figure 18, which illustrates the Value Network&#xD;
    associated to the AGR Business Model, presented in D1.3 as part of the Virtual Factory Network use case.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The figure shows the deliverable flows between the roles defined in the Business Model (Laboratory, Authority,&#xD;
    Regulator, etc.). In this view, roles are highlighted (ellipses), and activities (that consume and produce&#xD;
    deliverables) are hidden. Deliverable flows are depicted with arrows between the roles that perform the activities that&#xD;
    produce or consume such flows. The name of the deliverable (i.e. Business Item) is shown next to the arrow.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
